title: Return on average ordinary shareholders ' equity at HSBC 2009 to 2019
summary: The Return of equity the HSBC of ( NAR ) has steadily increased since 2012 , reaching a membership of 10.9 % in 2011 , an all-time high .
This trend also reflects the recovery of the property market after the financial crisis of 2007 - 2009 , as the volume of home sales began to climb from 2011 .
The NAR is a North American trade HSBC for real estate workers formed in 1908 and currently based in Chicago , Illinois .
